Package ohos.wearable.tile

Enum TileStatus

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<TileStatus>
      • ohos.wearable.tile.TileStatus
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ohos.utils.Sequenceable

    public enum TileStatus
extends java.lang.Enum<TileStatus>
implements ohos.utils.Sequenceable
    Enumerates states of a tile.

    A tile has various states in its lifecycle. When the tile state changes, TileAbility#onStatusChanged(TileStatus) is called to notify the TileAbility, so that different operations are performed as defined.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • TILE_PREPARE

        public static final TileStatus TILE_PREPARE
        Indicates that the tile is in the preparing state. Specifically, when a user selects a tile, the system automatically identifies the next possible tile to select and passes TILE_PREPARE to the TileAbility, so that the tile has time to prepare the data to display.

      • TILE_SELECTED

        public static final TileStatus TILE_SELECTED
        Indicates that the tile is in the selected state. Specifically, when a user selects the possible tile, the system passes TILE_SELECTED to the TileAbility, which returns the tile data to display.

      • TILE_HIDE

        public static final TileStatus TILE_HIDE
        Indicates that the tile is in the hidden state when a user releases the tile. In this case, the TileAbility should clear the data to reduce system load.

      • TILE_UPDATE

        public static final TileStatus TILE_UPDATE
        Indicates that the tile is in the updated state. In this case, a valid TileEntity object should be returned. The system passes TILE_UPDATE to the TileAbility in the following cases:
        • This tile is added to the visible list.
        • The TileAbility calls TileAbility#notifyDataChanged(Context, ElementName).
        • The delay in updating this tile is set via TileEntity.Builder.setUpdateDelay(long) and the delay elapses.
